If there is no note in the CLASS NOTES section of classes.berkeley.edu page, then presume it is NOT being webcast. I specifically asked faculty to let me know that information so I could share it with you all but never heard back from prof for CS 168.
In the notes it says "* Time conflicts with this class WILL be allowed by the Computer Science department." If time conflicts are allowed should we assume it's being webcasted?
No, I would not assume that at all. If you want to know if 168 will be webcast, you will have to ask the professor since we have been given no information regarding that.
Is 168 still being offered next semester?

For now, I recommend that you be patient. Phase 2 doesn't end until January 5th which leaves plenty of time for this matter to be resolved. Rest assured, faculty are aware of the issue and it's being worked behind the scenes...along with other issues regarding staffing for SP20 classes.
If we are interested in taking CS W186, and it hasn't been released by the Phase 2 deadline, what do you recommend we do?

I cannot say. I recommend that you check on classes.berkeley.edu for CHEM C191 for more information. Specifically, if you can find a website for the SP20 version of the class you'll probably find your answers. If not, contact teaching faculty.
